reviews.review_text: Not bad Being I was born during this show it has particular interest to me.  Awesome show, and I've heard a few recordings of it.  But this is the only one I've seen in its entirety.  Not the best sound quality, and I know there were other tapers there who got a better sample.  Maybe someday they'll find there way here too.

Great show. There is a SBD out there. The second set in particular is definitely worth having. I have a complete SBD of set 2 and part of set 1. Source: SBD > Kidd MC > D. I'm sure a complete SBD is out there somewhere. Anyone?
I dont think so While the music is great here, the sound quality is poor.  I do not reccomend the dl at all unless there is another source. 3 because there never was a bad dead show...Peace
Wow Have over 8000+ hrs in my collection & seen many GD shows i will have to say this 2nd set blasts off & the boys don't stop till the end . All i can say its worth having

AUD source There is NOTHING wrong with this AUD source.  If you are seeking a pristine SBD, look elsewhere.  If you want to know what it must have been like (and, note, I would have been 1 year old at the time) to experience a show in 1973 from the ~30th row with people talking to you and enjoying it with you, this is just about perfect.

- Can't say the same about this night that I did about the previous. Same cloudy AUD quality, nowhere near as good a show. Actually, because the AUD is quite a bit worse than the last night's, I don't know if I can even hear whether the show's any good or not. Certainly not good enough for a road trip.

Denver 73 This is a hot show. Yeah they start off as usual with their great first set. Then they just take off with the 2nd set none stop. If your into the 73 tour like I am this concert is on fire. Jerry, Bob and Phil are on top of it right to the last song. SWEET.
